title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theater on 1982-02-16
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil-> Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O-> Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, Looks Like Rain, Might As Well

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Black Peter-> Playin' In The Band-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

Benefit Concert

reviews.review_text: dolby Took a solid listening to sections of Terrapin and Althea of both of these audience recordings and am choosing the other one to download. If you do not mind the slight choked off feeling and sound of the dolby on a recording then this one is your puppy. I sooooo wish the playback deck was indeed the Sony TC D-5m with the same exact dolby b rather than the Nakamichi Dragon playback source-THAT  I believe would have made the difference for me between this NAK300 fine recording and the other NAK700 fine recording.
Good recording A smokin' show in a smokin' year.

WTF why would anyone post such a shitty recording?
sounds like someone taped it in their pants pocket,
terrible

Great show to start an underrated year To answer the question of who would post this horrible sounding aud and why:
1) This is a historical record of the first show of '82. That alone should be reason enough.
2) There is clearly no soundboard of this show circulating, so this is all we have.
3) The sound is actually not bad for an aud, try the NOLA 1980 October shows if you want a real 'pocket recording' sound.
4) Some if us enjoy decent auds as they give us a chance to feel the atmosphere differently than a soundboard.
BTW: THE DRAGON BEATS THE SONY
